  link     github.com/theminji/VType

  TTS MCP Server
  stack    Python / MCP / AI
  about    A simple text-to-speech MCP server for local AI to generate speech files with.
            I was shocked that LM Studio didn't have any local TTS servers, so I created one.
            It uses Supertonic-2 TTS for the backend, which runs faster than realtime!
  link     github.com/theminji/tts-mcp

  Lemod AI Discord moderator
  stack    Python / Discord.py / OpenAI Moderation Toolkit
  about    I created a Discord bot that utilizes the OpenAI moderation toolkit to automatically
            moderate users, and also allows for admin command using natural language
            via LLM tool calls. This bot was developed specifically for the MattVidPro AI Discord server.
  link     discord.gg/mattvidpro

  OpenGoody-2 LLM
  stack    Python / Unsloth / AI Training
  about    I fine tuned Qwen3.5 4b on my local hardware to replicate the closed source Goody-2 AI model.
            The goal of the model is to safetymaxx the AI to prevent harmful responses,
            but it is SOOO safetymaxxed that it refuses any prompt. That's the fun of the model.
  link     hf.co/theminji/OpenGoody-2

